# Windsurf Rules

# Source of truth lives in `AGENTS.md` and the `.ai/` folder. Read those.
# Edit content there, not in this file.

## Read first

- `AGENTS.md` — universal agent entry-point (project summary, top rules)
- `.ai/project.md` — project description, stack, run/test/build commands
- `.ai/rules.md` — hard do/don't rules

## Read on demand

- `.ai/architecture.md` — when changing structure or data flow
- `.ai/style.md` — when naming, formatting, or commenting
- `.ai/glossary.md` — when encountering unfamiliar domain terms
- `.ai/skills/add-feature.md` — for feature work
- `.ai/skills/fix-bug.md` — for bug fixes
- `.ai/skills/refactor.md` — for refactors
- `.ai/skills/write-tests.md` — for tests
- `.ai/decisions/` — for context on past architectural choices

## Behavior

- The "Never" list in `.ai/rules.md` is non-negotiable.
- Match local patterns over generic best practices. Read neighbor files
  before editing.
- Smallest correct change. No drive-by refactors bundled with task work.
- Run lint, typecheck, and tests (commands in `.ai/project.md`) before
  declaring work done.
